Quality Control Plots

Well make a UMAP of the ground truth labels for each dataset to make sure our data look halfway realistic.

qc_plots <- purrr::map(ls()[grepl("sim_", ls())], function(w) {
  seu <- eval(as.symbol(w))
  p <- DimPlot(seu, 
               group.by = "cellPopulation", 
               cols = alpha(paletteer::paletteer_d("ggsci::nrc_npg"), alpha = 0.5), 
               shuffle = TRUE, 
               seed = 312, 
               raster = FALSE,  
               pt.size = 1) + 
       labs(x = "UMAP 1", 
            y = "UMAP 2",
            title = paste0("Dataset: ", w), 
            color = "True Labels") + 
       theme_classic(base_size = 14) + 
       theme(axis.text = element_blank(), 
             axis.ticks = element_blank(), 
             plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5), 
             plot.title.position = "panel") + 
       guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(alpha = 1, size = 3)))
  return(p)
})

Lets check out each plot.

for (p in qc_plots) {
  print(p)
}
